Text: I think stagnant would be the right word to describe this weeks project progress on my end.

Coming into this project, I knew I would lack some expertise, but I've always had the goal to learn as much as possible for my own personal development and so I wouldn't be too much of a liability to the team.
This weeks project goals were to add finishing touches to our web pages and set up the QR codes to respective URLs and identifications.
At the beginning of the week, I researched some more web design theories and tried to implement 'Gestalt's principles' such as the golden ratio and finding inspiration from other web designs.

There were many things I wanted to do to correct the styling of the page, so I tried, in my own time, to create my own web page and do various modifications in an attempt to change shape and size etc.
Moral of the story is that there is a whole lot more I need to know and learn.
So, for now, the team is fixing necessary functionality aspects, like, the webpage responsiveness and embedding audio.

I think the takeaway from this week is that although I could not contribute in the HTML and CSS aspect of the webpage development, I enjoyed forcing myself to clue up, so I wouldn't be too in the dark about the process.
Very thankful for Bibi to run through the HTML code with me and for Yoko to teach me one or two things about HTML.

Although this week had been stagnant on my end, if faced with the same situation in the next project, I at least feel thankful that I have this project experience because now I have some what of an idea of the scope of a project like this.

I'm realising now that I am someone that likes to plan as much of the project upfront as possible to help organise my thoughts and thenÂ undergo changes during the project when necessary - this will be something I need to work on next time (perhaps that is why I feel anxious about the process).
Despite this, I've had a chance to work on developing my Java skills and equipping myself with the use of Github this week which is great.
Our goals for next week comprise of user testing.
We have goals to set up the QR codes.
Bibi got into contact with the IT guy of the museum end of last week, hence the delay in set up.
We need a working URL in order to attach a QR code to our product.
However, during Friday's meeting, we found out that Yoko has access to a domain, which is great!
So, she will be setting that up - then we will test our QR codes.
At the moment I am looking into developing a questionnaire for user testing, using heuristic evaluation (recommended by Teacher1's partner ;)), which will be interesting.
Guess we will see how we go!
Overall
